doc.after: Order Passeriformes Family Mimidae The mimids are a family of passerine birds which includes thrashers mockingbirds tremblers and the New World catbirds They are notable for their vocalization especially their remarkable ability to mimic a wide variety of birds and other sounds heard outdoors The species tend towards dull grays and browns in their appearance
